  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Grate approx. 250g <span class=\"text-danger\">[500g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>red cabbage</strong>, discarding the tough&nbsp;stem</p>\r\n<p>Add the&nbsp;<strong>grated cabbage</strong>&nbsp;to a very large bowl with the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside until later to pickle slightly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chickpeas</strong> to a baking tray with the<strong> ras el hanout</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong>&nbsp;(Can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until golden and crispy &ndash; these are your <strong>shawarma chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1363.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>pitta bread</strong> into rough triangles (pile them up to make it quicker!)</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped pitta</strong>&nbsp;to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the <strong>sumac</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 8-10 min or until golden and crispy &ndash; these are your <strong>sumac pitta chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
